18
00:03:42,372 --> 00:03:49,437
"...once again for those
days and nights of leisure..."

19
00:04:01,657 --> 00:04:03,284
Hello Sir.
- Hello.

20
00:04:03,393 --> 00:04:06,294
This is Mr. Chawla, our biggest
distributor in eastern India.

21
00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:09,294
How do you do sir?
Dr. Kamal Bose.

22
00:04:09,399 --> 00:04:10,627
How do you do?

23
00:04:10,733 --> 00:04:12,462
I know you well
by your medicines.

24
00:04:12,568 --> 00:04:14,502
That is why I am infamous.

25
00:04:15,405 --> 00:04:18,806
In fact all my doctor
friends prescribe your medicines.

26
00:04:18,908 --> 00:04:21,968
Nowadays your name
dominates the market. - Okay.

27
00:04:22,078 --> 00:04:25,479
Mr. Chawla, isn't your
head office in Calcutta?

28
00:04:25,581 --> 00:04:28,311
Yes. I had come here only to
arrange this cottage for you.

29
00:04:28,418 --> 00:04:30,318
Mr. Bali had called.

30
00:04:30,420 --> 00:04:31,910
Didn't Mr. Bali
mention over the phone that...

31
00:04:32,021 --> 00:04:33,488
...during these holidays
I do not wish to hear...

32
00:04:33,589 --> 00:04:34,647
...even the names of medicines?

33
00:04:34,757 --> 00:04:36,315
I want a
complete rest from work.

34
00:04:36,426 --> 00:04:37,916
Physical as well as mental.

35
00:04:38,027 --> 00:04:40,860
Neither do I want to tell
anything about them, nor hear.

36
00:04:46,702 --> 00:04:48,329
Whose cottage is this?

37
00:04:48,438 --> 00:04:50,838
Dinshaw Irani's. A Parsi
medicine man of Calcutta...

38
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:52,840
...who is now settled in Bombay.

39
00:04:54,043 --> 00:04:56,534
He has maintained
his house beautifully.

40
00:04:56,646 --> 00:04:58,409
Yes, that is the
uniqueness of the Parsis.

41
00:04:58,514 --> 00:05:01,347
Even if hundreds of years pass
by, their wallpapers don't spoil.

42
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:09,354
Greetings, sir... Greetings.

43
00:05:09,459 --> 00:05:11,689
I have heard you are very
fond of eating and drinking.

44
00:05:11,794 --> 00:05:15,025
So I have arranged this cook
for you. He cooks very well.

45
00:05:27,477 --> 00:05:29,707
The twin pills of
Gill's medicines.

46
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:32,778
You can have them with
either water or milk.

47
00:05:32,882 --> 00:05:35,544
They provide relief from
cold and cough immediately.

48
00:05:37,487 --> 00:05:39,921
These medicines do
not leave me here also.

49
00:05:40,022 --> 00:05:42,456
They are medicines
discovered by you, Dr. Gill.

50
00:05:42,758 --> 00:05:47,559
Yes, where am I refusing that?
My deeds are chasing me.

51
00:05:47,663 --> 00:05:49,722
They don't leave me at all.

52
00:05:58,841 --> 00:06:00,399
Beautiful!

53
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:02,569
Is this the first time you
have come to Darjeeling?

54
00:06:03,112 --> 00:06:07,572
No, I have come once
before also. Many years ago.

55
00:06:07,683 --> 00:06:12,746
About 25 years ago. Before I
gave my doctor's examination.

56
00:06:13,523 --> 00:06:15,753
Then I had an accident.

57
00:06:15,858 --> 00:06:20,591
Accident? - Yes! I had
fallen in love with a girl.

58
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:26,424
Oh! That happens in youth, doctor
I also had them. - With her?

59
00:06:26,536 --> 00:06:28,936
Yes. I mean, no. It was on
the hill station and now...

60
00:06:29,038 --> 00:06:31,836
...I am the father
of her three kids.

61
00:06:31,974 --> 00:06:35,102
No, man, I did not do
anything like that with her.

62
00:06:35,211 --> 00:06:37,941
That is why you were saved
and I had to get married.

63
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:45,518
Listen.
- Yes sir.

64
00:06:45,621 --> 00:06:47,782
What is your name?
- Mangal Singh sir.

65
00:06:47,890 --> 00:06:51,121
Mangal Singh sir?
- No sir, only Mangal Singh.

66
00:06:51,827 --> 00:06:54,796
Tell someone to put the chairs
out. We shall sit there only.

67
00:06:54,897 --> 00:06:59,129
Excuse me, Dr. Gill.
I'll take your leave now.

68
00:06:59,235 --> 00:07:01,465
I have work in the hospital.
I'll meet in the evening.

69
00:07:01,571 --> 00:07:03,129
Okay.
- Mr. Chawla?

70
00:07:03,239 --> 00:07:05,639
Mr. Chawla, you too may leave.
No need for formalities.

71
00:07:05,741 --> 00:07:08,073
I'll take some rest now.
We'll meet in the evening.

72
00:07:08,177 --> 00:07:11,146
Bye for now. We'll
meet in the evening.

73
00:07:11,247 --> 00:07:15,809
If you need me for anything,
here's my card. Come on.

74
00:07:29,599 --> 00:07:30,998
Dhyan Singh...
- Yes sir?

75
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:33,500
Why are you throwing
cold water on the car...

76
00:07:33,603 --> 00:07:35,833
...early in the morning? I am
feeling cold just by its sight.

77
00:07:35,938 --> 00:07:37,098
Don't you feel anything?

78
00:07:37,206 --> 00:07:39,834
It's better if I wash it now
only. If the master asks for it...

79
00:07:39,942 --> 00:07:41,500
...as soon as he wakes up,
then what shall I do?

80
00:07:41,877 --> 00:07:44,175
This is not
Calcutta; this is Darjeeling.

81
00:07:44,614 --> 00:07:46,582
Dr. Gill has come
here on vacation.

82
00:07:46,682 --> 00:07:48,707
He'll not wake up so soon.

83
00:07:48,818 --> 00:07:50,513
Yes, this is the
condition since yesterday.

84
00:07:50,620 --> 00:07:53,521
I myself was
waiting till 11 o'clock.

85
00:07:54,624 --> 00:07:56,524
When will the
master have breakfast?

86
00:07:56,626 --> 00:07:58,526
Today the master will
have a very heavy breakfast.

87
00:07:58,628 --> 00:08:00,528
He has not eaten
anything since yesterday.

88
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:02,928
When will he have it?
- As soon as he wakes up.

89
00:08:03,633 --> 00:08:05,601
Who will wake up?
- The master.

90
00:08:05,701 --> 00:08:08,534
Early morning, the master...

91
00:08:09,639 --> 00:08:11,869
Now this hill
station has changed a lot.

92
00:08:11,974 --> 00:08:14,534
When I had come
here many years ago...

93
00:08:14,644 --> 00:08:16,703
...there weren't
so many cars here.

94
00:08:16,912 --> 00:08:19,608
There were only mostly
rickshaws plying here.

95
00:08:19,715 --> 00:08:22,548
Now it is not even the season.
When the season comes...

96
00:08:22,652 --> 00:08:24,552
...you shall see, there's
so much rush here that...

97
00:08:24,654 --> 00:08:26,554
...people do not even get
adequate place to stay.

98
00:08:27,923 --> 00:08:30,949
Then we could manage to get
lodging at someone's house...

99
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:33,551
...as a paying guest even.
I myself had stayed...

100
00:08:33,663 --> 00:08:36,223
...at a contractor's place.
Mr... Mr. Jodhpal.

101
00:08:38,934 --> 00:08:40,902
Do you know what the
rent of the room was?

102
00:08:41,003 --> 00:08:42,561
Seven rupees.

103
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:45,570
But sir, now that
can be only dreamt of.

104
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:49,574
Right said! The whole
place looked different then.

105
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:55,080
See that wood shed there?
- Yes.

106
00:08:55,951 --> 00:08:58,579
There used to be a
doctor's shop there.

107
00:08:58,688 --> 00:09:00,781
When had you come here before?

108
00:09:00,890 --> 00:09:02,755
It is many years now.

109
00:09:02,958 --> 00:09:06,257
But we are seeing this shed
here like this since many years.

110
00:09:06,696 --> 00:09:09,096
I am talking of a
time before that.

111
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,668
You must be mistaken.

112
00:09:12,768 --> 00:09:16,602
No. I cannot be
mistaken about this place.

113
00:09:17,973 --> 00:09:19,998
A little ahead from here,
there are those stairs, isn't it?

114
00:09:20,109 --> 00:09:21,770
Those which descend
from the Upper Bazaar?

115
00:09:21,877 --> 00:09:24,107
Yes.
- Then this is the same place.

116
00:09:24,213 --> 00:09:27,114
But sir, there was
never a doctor's shop here.

117
00:09:27,216 --> 00:09:28,945
We have always
seen this shed here.

118
00:09:29,051 --> 00:09:31,611
You must be talking
of the doctor Thapa.

119
00:09:32,988 --> 00:09:36,947
Yes, yes, he's the
one. Harihar Thapa.

120
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:39,957
It's ages since he died, sir.

121
00:09:40,730 --> 00:09:43,961
But he was not that old.

122
00:09:44,066 --> 00:09:46,125
Does it take time
to grow old, sir?

123
00:09:46,402 --> 00:09:49,303
If there is sorrow,
man can age very quickly.

124
00:09:49,405 --> 00:09:51,305
Which sorrow did he have?

125
00:09:51,407 --> 00:09:53,967
The sorrow of a
daughter is very bad, sir.

126
00:09:54,076 --> 00:09:58,240
He had a young girl. She
had a very pretty name...

127
00:09:58,748 --> 00:10:03,185
Chanda? - Yes, Chanda. You
have a sharp memory, sir.

128
00:10:04,019 --> 00:10:07,648
Then?
- She wouldn't marry. - Why?

129
00:10:08,023 --> 00:10:10,651
She would tell some
doctor would come to take her.

130
00:10:15,097 --> 00:10:16,155
Then?

131
00:10:16,265 --> 00:10:20,167
Does anyone come back, sir?
She was humiliated in society.

132
00:10:20,269 --> 00:10:22,999
We don't know who the man
who gave her sorrow was.

133
00:10:23,205 --> 00:10:25,730
The doctor also stuck to
the bed in such a way...

134
00:10:25,841 --> 00:10:29,675
...that he died on the bed
itself. Only before dying...

135
00:10:29,779 --> 00:10:32,077
...he entrusted his daughter
to a lame stammering man.

136
00:10:32,782 --> 00:10:35,683
Lame? Stammering?

137
00:10:35,785 --> 00:10:38,754
Yes. He was staying
down in the Blue Valley.

138
00:10:39,054 --> 00:10:41,682
A factory had opened
up there that time.

139
00:10:41,791 --> 00:10:44,021
We had heard Chanda
also worked there.

140
00:10:44,226 --> 00:10:47,195
When she returned home
upon her father's death...

141
00:10:47,296 --> 00:10:50,231
...she had a child in her arms.
Her husband did not come.

142
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:54,096
Some tell he died;
some tell he left her.

143
00:11:17,927 --> 00:11:20,395
Show that to me...
- Here.

144
00:11:26,836 --> 00:11:29,396
Show me that one. - That
one's mine. - Show it please.

145
00:12:28,898 --> 00:12:31,196
What happened? Did
you have a fall?

146
00:12:32,434 --> 00:12:34,129
Yes. This...

147
00:12:34,904 --> 00:12:36,872
Is it a sprain or an injury?

148
00:12:36,972 --> 00:12:39,202
I do not know.
Perhaps it is a sprain.

149
00:12:39,308 --> 00:12:41,799
There's a doctor here. Get
him to put an ointment on it.

150
00:12:41,911 --> 00:12:44,379
It will be well in an instant.
- Is that so?

151
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,141
He is a very good doctor. Yes.

152
00:12:57,359 --> 00:12:59,827
Did you bring the herbs?
Which all did you get?

153
00:13:00,195 --> 00:13:04,359
I found some of them. And I
also found a patient, father.

154
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:07,161
He has a sprain in his
foot. He'll come now...

155
00:13:07,269 --> 00:13:08,896
...to get an ointment put on it.

156
00:13:09,004 --> 00:13:12,167
Those stairs in the bazaar.
He fell on them.

157
00:13:12,274 --> 00:13:14,242
Did he fall by himself
or did you push him?

158
00:13:14,343 --> 00:13:16,038
Why will I push him?

159
00:13:16,378 --> 00:13:19,836
Who knows? You may be
helping your father's business.

160
00:13:20,215 --> 00:13:23,116
Very good! If someone falls,
that means I have pushed him.

161
00:13:23,218 --> 00:13:25,186
Don't know what he thinks of me!

162
00:13:35,965 --> 00:13:40,197
Come, come, come. Did
you sprain your leg?

163
00:13:40,302 --> 00:13:44,033
Yes. It seems like that.

164
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:50,273
It is the fault of the eyes,
and the legs have to suffer.

165
00:13:50,379 --> 00:13:55,043
A foolish leader commits a
folly; the whole village pays.

166
00:13:56,986 --> 00:13:59,045
Give me your foot.

167
00:14:01,323 --> 00:14:05,054
So you slipped on
the bazaar steps?

168
00:14:06,261 --> 00:14:08,559
It doesn't matter.
You are saved.

169
00:14:08,664 --> 00:14:11,224
If you had been hit on the
head, that would be grave.

170
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:14,302
Chanda, bring the
herbal oil kept inside.

171
00:14:14,403 --> 00:14:16,496
I'm warming and
bringing it, father.

172
00:14:16,605 --> 00:14:18,573
Shall I bring the turmeric also.

173
00:14:18,674 --> 00:14:20,232
Yes, bring that also.

174
00:14:21,543 --> 00:14:23,067
Did you see? Before
the patient comes...

175
00:14:23,178 --> 00:14:25,078
...the preparation of
the medicine has begun.

176
00:14:25,180 --> 00:14:29,241
Do you know astrology also?

177
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,246
Yes, I know.

178
00:14:38,293 --> 00:14:42,252
Okay! So that's how you
came to know about it.

179
00:14:42,364 --> 00:14:44,992
Seen her? She's my astrologer.

180
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:46,931
She keeps herself updated
with the goings-on of the city.

181
00:14:47,036 --> 00:14:50,437
From where have you come?
- From Calcutta.

182
00:14:51,373 --> 00:14:55,104
What is your name?
- Amar Nath Gill.

183
00:14:55,310 --> 00:14:58,473
What are you doing?
- Learning to be a doctor.

184
00:14:58,580 --> 00:15:01,344
It is the last year so I
have come here for preparation.

185
00:15:01,450 --> 00:15:05,113
"Whether you take
a prescription.".

186
00:15:05,220 --> 00:15:07,120
"...or rely on drugs..."

187
00:15:07,322 --> 00:15:09,222
"A man has to face the
consequences of his deeds."

188
00:15:09,324 --> 00:15:11,292
"Whatever he does, the
doctor ends up getting richer."

189
00:15:13,062 --> 00:15:15,292
If you do not have the
sole intent of earning money...

190
00:15:15,397 --> 00:15:18,298
...then there is no occupation
better than this, Amar Nath.

191
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:21,164
Amar Nath what?
- Gill.

192
00:15:21,336 --> 00:15:22,963
There is so much
pleasure in this job that...

193
00:15:23,072 --> 00:15:25,973
...it cannot be expressed in
words. It is like worship.

194
00:15:26,075 --> 00:15:28,305
That is why I am
learning to be a doctor.

195
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:30,702
So you'll open your
clinic in the city?

196
00:15:30,813 --> 00:15:33,145
It won't work in the village.
- Why?

197
00:15:33,248 --> 00:15:36,149
Who will buy such expensive
medicines here, Amar Nath?

198
00:15:36,351 --> 00:15:37,978
Gill!

199
00:15:38,087 --> 00:15:40,715
Yes, Gill. Here only
our herbs will work.

200
00:15:41,090 --> 00:15:43,490
The virtues are
earned by the tree...

201
00:15:43,592 --> 00:15:45,583
...while the peepal
tree has to sacrifice.

202
00:15:46,095 --> 00:15:49,326
Where's a doctor like me
who can take care of all?

203
00:15:50,099 --> 00:15:52,329
Once I have the knowledge, sir...

204
00:15:52,434 --> 00:15:54,402
...I shall learn
the wisdom from you.

205
00:15:55,104 --> 00:15:56,401
Where do you stay here?

206
00:15:56,638 --> 00:15:59,664
That bungalow of the contractor
Jodhpal... I stay there only.

207
00:15:59,775 --> 00:16:01,174
That is very near.

208
00:16:01,276 --> 00:16:03,176
Father, the bandage.

209
00:16:03,278 --> 00:16:08,181
Okay, so you stay in
Jodhpal's bungalow. - Yes.

210
00:16:08,283 --> 00:16:13,220
Anyway that remains
vacant ten months in a year.

211
00:16:15,457 --> 00:16:17,084
Where do you eat?

212
00:16:17,192 --> 00:16:19,353
In a wayside restaurant.

213
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:24,760
How bad! Being a student, you
eat in a wayside restaurant?

214
00:16:24,867 --> 00:16:27,358
How will you top
your class then?

215
00:16:28,137 --> 00:16:33,097
No, no, no. From today
you'll eat with us. Okay Chanda?

216
00:16:33,208 --> 00:16:37,372
Thank you. How much?

217
00:16:38,147 --> 00:16:42,049
Let it be. First you become
all right, Amar Nath... - Gill.

218
00:16:42,584 --> 00:16:45,451
I'll take the money later.
When you come to dine at night...

219
00:16:45,554 --> 00:16:47,112
...l'll change the bandage.

220
00:16:48,423 --> 00:16:50,391
Thank you. Good bye.

221
00:16:56,498 --> 00:17:01,060
Take care, take care. Take my
stick. Chanda, give my stick.

222
00:17:11,180 --> 00:17:13,580
Bring in the evening
without fail. - Okay.

223
00:17:22,524 --> 00:17:25,755
Father, the
sprained one hasn't come.

224
00:17:26,195 --> 00:17:28,163
May I give his
share to the goat?

225
00:17:28,263 --> 00:17:31,255
Why? Did you eat the
hay meant for the goat?

226
00:17:31,466 --> 00:17:35,425
Am I an animal to eat
the fodder of animals?

227
00:17:35,537 --> 00:17:37,437
Then why will you give
his share to the goat?

228
00:17:37,539 --> 00:17:39,166
Does the goat
also have a sprain?

229
00:17:40,209 --> 00:17:42,109
What is there
about a sprain in this?

230
00:17:46,215 --> 00:17:48,615
Always doing charity.
You don't take money from...

231
00:17:48,717 --> 00:17:52,448
...the villagers because they
are from the same village.

232
00:17:53,555 --> 00:17:59,289
You found one foreigner, but
he too turned to be a student.

233
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:03,196
More than a student, he
has become something else.

234
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:09,129
How will it do if you
treat everyone for free?

235
00:18:09,671 --> 00:18:13,129
You have to get me married
in the future. What then?

236
00:18:13,242 --> 00:18:14,470
Don't get married.

237
